Cook potatoes in boiling water in large saucepan 20 min. or until tender; drain. Return to pan. Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Add margarine and sour cream to potatoes; mash until smooth. Spoon half into 1.5-L casserole dish; cover with layers of cheese, remaining potato mixture and bacon. Bake 30 to 35 min. or until heated through.